ugh 60 can be attacked and killed by each other, if of opposite teams.  There's no such thing as play nice policy here.  No rules against camping corpses, training people, etc.  I'd call it an &quot;anything goes&quot; server. <p>--Hagus Bruichladdich<BR><BR>"Tilt woon bock weth me dog!!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/8/02 9:55:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1923.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new &quot;anything goes&quot; server?</span><hr size=1> I actually have a small HIE enchanter on Sullon Zek (it ain't easy being Good on SZ, either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  I've actually found playing on the server a great deal of fun in my off-hours, and while yes, nearly annything goes, this actually cuts down on the whining a great deal. Enchanters make a great class to sniff around this server with, as we get Invis at level 4 (and you don't become PvP eligible until L 6, although folks can always train you), and Illusion: dark-elf and See Invisible at L 8.  Certain skills that are ignored on 'blue' servers (such as languages) are an essential to life on SZ; my little chanter is already fluent in Tier'dal and Dark Speech, thanks to the infiltration work of another enchanter there (and I might add that he picked up some of his skill through the creative use of Minor Illusion).<br><br>If you like PvP servers, and really can handle the whole corpse camping, random sudden pointless PKing, etc, thing (and I have seen some really creative ambushes set up just in the short time I have spent there), it wouldn't hurt to check it out.  Some people really get into the whole 'teams' thing, and some... just don't care.<br><br>Regards,<br>Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>Autonomous Collective <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uyuegouwindwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yuegou Windwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/10/02 12:13:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1923.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new &quot;anything goes&quot; server?</span><hr size=1> You are not safe at 5th level and lower, you are only safe at those levels in newbie zones. You leave the newbie zones and you can be pked at 1st level. There are only 2 zones that you cannot pk in, the Bazaar and the Nexus. <br><br>Sullon Zek is a server full of cowardice and revenge. 60th levels kill in newbie zones repeatedly, the newbies get bigger and the cycle repeats itself. It takes alot of will power and drive to remain on SZ, especially if you come from a "blue" server.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unydiaywalmoriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nydia Ywalmoriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(3/10/02 2:12:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1923.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new &quot;anything goes&quot; server?</span><hr size=1> Yup, I was in there the other day when 3 50+ Iksar ported into Gfay and started laying waste to the place.<br>For a few minutes, anyway... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The addition of Luclin made that type of thing *much* more frequent; since the Nexus is non PK, folks can now get from continent to continent directly from an area that they control without having to find a wizard or druid (more difficult for Evils, but Good controls few rings).  Since Gfay and Toxx are both newbie zones, they get hammered the hardest, but in general most of the rings/spires are flash/ambush points.<br><br>Like I said, it sucks to be Good on SZ <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  You have to have a high chaos tolerance, and a thick skin, to enjoy life there (and yes, the scum of the earth is on that server), but I find that it makes a nice diversion from time to time.  If I was going to do a 'serious' PvP character, I'd go to Rallos, but the politics, etc, involved with being in a PvP guild would take up *way* too time, as I am a tactics/politics freak.  <br><br>Regards,<br>Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>Autonomous Collective  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1923.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1923.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1923.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% borde